export const Questions = [
  {
    prompt: "What command is used to start the React local development server?",
    optionA: "npm serve",
    optionB: "npm run dev",
    optionC: "npm start",
    optionD: "npm build",
    answer: "C",
  },
  {
    prompt:
      "What is the default local host port that a React development server uses?",
    optionA: "3500",
    optionB: "5000",
    optionC: "3000",
    optionD: "8080",
    answer: "C",
  },
  {
    prompt: "To develop and run React code, Node.js is required.",
    optionA: "True",
    optionB: "False",
    answer: "A",
  },
  {
    prompt: "Which keyword creates a constant in JavaScript?",
    optionA: "const",
    optionB: "let",
    optionC: "constant",
    optionD: "var",
    answer: "A",
  },
  {
    prompt:
      "Which operator can be used to conditionally render a React component?",
    optionA: "??",
    optionB: "||",
    optionC: "::",
    optionD: "&&",
    answer: "D",
  },

  {
    prompt: "What tool does React use to compile JSX?",
    optionA: "React Router",
    optionB: "ReactDOM",
    optionC: "Babel",
    optionD: "JSX Compiler",
    answer: "C",
  },

  {
    prompt: "React can only render elements in the root document element.",
    optionA: "True",
    optionB: "False",
    answer: "B",
  },
];
